'''Ionite''' was a very rare and valuable material, found on [[Bandomeer/Legends|Bandomeer]].<ref name="GATORW">''[[Geonosis and the Outer Rim Worlds]]''</ref> Inherently ionite interfered with energy fields, such as [[Deflector shield/Legends|deflector shields]], due to its ability to hold neither a positive nor a negative charge, but rather an alternate charge. In the presence of positively charged elements, it carried a negative charge that negated the positive charge, and vice versa.<ref name="The Last Jedi">[[The Last Jedi (novel)|''The Last Jedi'']]</ref> Any electronic device in its proximity was thus voided and ruined, a notable example of this being that any timers in its vicinity were shut down (a notable problem for [[Mining/Legends|miners]], who could thus run out of air while mining it without realizing what was happening to them).

However, it was found that if concentrated correctly, ionite could be refined and made into a compound with varying explosive materials to make ionite [[Weapon/Legends|weapons]]. Though never fully exploited by a naval power, what ionite did come into the possession of willing powers could be turned into [[Grenade/Legends|grenades]], [[Bomb/Legends|bombs]], and [[Missile/Legends|missiles]] with the power to completely deplete shields, and render opponents completely defenseless.

